title.narrative: Capacity of services providers to provide quality and integrated health, HIV, nutrition, education, sanitation, birth registration and child protection services improved

description.narrative: In 2019, 1187 service providers of critical interventions in Health, Nutrition, WASH, eMTCT of HIV, Birth Registration, and ECD were capacitated to provide quality services through targeted trainings. Information systems were strengthened, and life-saving supplies and commodities provided to manage acute malnutrition and improve newborn health outcomes in five regions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/12/2019
